        "___\n",
        "**1. Write a Python program to create a bar graph that displays the population of five\n",
        "different cities. Customize the bar graph by adding a title, labels for the axes, and\n",
        "different colors for each bar.**\n",
        "___"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/",
          "height": 472
        },
        "id": "D-HFWC-WkLz1",
        "outputId": "3af7200f-17c6-45aa-92f4-93997f2a3a37"
      },
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "display_data",
          "data": {
            "text/plain": [
              "<Figure size 640x480 with 1 Axes>"
            ],
            "image/png": "\n"
          },
          "metadata": {}
        }
      ],
      "source": [
        "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
        "#data\n",
        "cities = ['New York', 'Los Angeles', 'Chicago', 'Houston', 'Phoenix']\n",
        "populations = [8419000, 3980000, 2716000, 2328000, 1690000]\n",
        "\n",
        "#Code here\n",
        "# Colors for each bar\n",
        "colors = ['blue', 'green', 'red', 'purple', 'orange']\n",
        "\n",
        "# Plotting the bar graph\n",
        "plt.bar(cities, populations, color=colors)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Adding title and labels\n",
        "plt.title('Population of Five Cities')\n",
        "plt.xlabel('Cities')\n",
        "plt.ylabel('Population')\n",
        "\n",
        "# Displaying the plot\n",
        "plt.show()"
      ]
    },

      "source": [
        "___\n",
        "**2. Write a Python program to create a pie chart that represents the market share\n",
        " of different smartphone brands. Label each wedge with the brand name and percentage, and\n",
        " highlight (explode) the wedge representing higher market share.**\n",
        " ___"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/",
          "height": 428
        },
        "id": "z5pwHXvLkLz3",
        "outputId": "b6094bb8-27fe-4115-802a-6b85a60fd30e"
      },
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "display_data",
          "data": {
            "text/plain": [
              "<Figure size 640x480 with 1 Axes>"
            ],
            "image/png": "\n"
          },
          "metadata": {}
        }
      ],
      "source": [
        "# Data\n",
        "brands = ['Apple', 'Samsung', 'Huawei', 'Xiaomi', 'Oppo']\n",
        "market_share = [27.5, 21.3, 15.8, 10.5, 8.3]\n",
        "\n",
        "#Code here\n",
        "\n",
        "# Determine the index of the highest market share\n",
        "max_index = market_share.index(max(market_share))\n",
        "\n",
        "# Create an explode list, with a 0.1 offset for the highest market share\n",
        "explode = [0.1 if i == max_index else 0 for i in range(len(market_share))]\n",
        "\n",
        "# Plotting the pie chart\n",
        "plt.pie(market_share, labels=brands, autopct='%1.1f%%', explode=explode, shadow=True, startangle=140)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Adding title\n",
        "plt.title('Market Share of Smartphone Brands')\n",
        "\n",
        "# Displaying the plot\n",
        "plt.show()"
      ]
    },

        "___"

          "metadata": {}
        }
      ],
      "source": [
        "# Data\n",
        "quarters = ['Q1', 'Q2', 'Q3', 'Q4']\n",
        "product1_sales = [150, 200, 250, 300]\n",
        "product2_sales = [100, 150, 200, 250]\n",
        "product3_sales = [50, 100, 150, 200]\n",
        "\n",
        "#Code here\n",
        "\n",
        "# Plotting\n",
        "plt.bar(quarters, product1_sales, color='red', label='Product 1')\n",
        "plt.bar(quarters, product2_sales, bottom=product1_sales, color='green', label='Product 2')\n",
        "plt.bar(quarters, product3_sales, bottom=[i+j for i,j in zip(product1_sales, product2_sales)], color='blue', label='Product 3')\n",
        "\n",
        "# Adding labels and legend\n",
        "plt.title('Sales of Products by Quarter')\n",
        "plt.xlabel('Quarters')\n",
        "plt.ylabel('Sales')\n",
        "plt.legend()\n",
        "\n",
        "# Displaying the plot\n",
        "plt.show()"
      ]

        "**19. Using the Titanic dataset create a figure with two subplots: one subplot showing a histogram of the 'age' column with 50 bins and the second subplot showing a bar chart of the 'pclass' column. Ensure that both plots share the same x-axis.**\n",
        "___"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/",

        },
        "id": "nTm8fkDekLz9",
        "outputId": "27919a99-e64d-42ad-ffef-d4d0c753e2ae"
      },
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "display_data",
          "data": {
            "text/plain": [
              "<Figure size 1200x1200 with 2 Axes>"
            ],
            "image/png": "\n"
          },
          "metadata": {}
        }
      ],
      "source": [
        "#Code here\n",
        "\n",
        "fig, (ax1, ax2) = plt.subplots(2, 1, figsize=(12, 12), sharex=True)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Histogram of 'age'\n",
        "ax1.hist(titanic['age'].dropna(), bins=50, color='skyblue')\n",
        "ax1.set_title(\"Age Distribution\", fontsize=15)\n",
        "ax1.set_ylabel(\"Frequency\", fontsize=13)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Bar chart of 'pclass'\n",
        "pclass_counts = titanic['pclass'].value_counts()\n",
        "ax2.bar(pclass_counts.index, pclass_counts.values, color='lightgreen')\n",
        "ax2.set_title(\"Passenger Class Distribution\", fontsize=15)\n",
        "ax2.set_xlabel(\"Class\", fontsize=13)\n",
        "ax2.set_ylabel(\"Count\", fontsize=13)\n",
        "\n",
        "plt.show()\n"
      ]
    },

      "source": [
        "___\n",
        "**20. Using the Titanic dataset create a figure with two subplots: the first subplot should display a line plot of the 'age' column, and the second subplot should display a bar chart of the 'sex' column showing the count of each gender.**\n",
        "___"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/",
          "height": 958
        },
        "id": "AVGhTZo0kL0C",
        "outputId": "8a6c6b6f-26b9-4559-dd00-62ce65e6bab2"
      },
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "display_data",
          "data": {
            "text/plain": [
              "<Figure size 1200x1200 with 2 Axes>"
            ],
            "image/png": "\n"
          },
          "metadata": {}
        }
      ],
      "source": [
        "#Code here\n",
        "\n",
        "fig, (ax1, ax2) = plt.subplots(2, 1, figsize=(12, 12))\n",
        "\n",
        "# Line plot of 'age'\n",
        "titanic['age'].plot(ax=ax1, linestyle='-', color='blue')\n",
        "ax1.set_title(\"Age Plot\", fontsize=15)\n",
        "ax1.set_xlabel(\"Passenger No\", fontsize=13)\n",
        "ax1.set_ylabel(\"Age\", fontsize=13)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Bar chart of 'sex'\n",
        "sex_counts = titanic['sex'].value_counts()\n",
        "sex_counts.plot(kind='bar', ax=ax2, color=['lightblue', 'pink'])\n",
        "ax2.set_title(\"Gender Distribution\", fontsize=15)\n",
        "ax2.set_xlabel(\"Gender\", fontsize=13)\n",
        "ax2.set_ylabel(\"Count\", fontsize=13)\n",
        "\n",
        "plt.tight_layout()\n",
        "plt.show()\n"
      ]
    },
